1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:01,300
<i> Set to 200 joules.</i>

2
00:00:01,633 --> 00:00:02,633
<i> Clear?</i>

3
00:00:02,633 --> 00:00:03,733
<i>- Clear.
- Clear.</i>

4
00:00:04,367 --> 00:00:05,767
[DOCTOR] Mrs. Almazan?

5
00:00:05,767 --> 00:00:07,133
<i> Endaya?</i>

6
00:00:07,133 --> 00:00:09,267
<i> We did everything we could.</i>

7
00:00:09,767 --> 00:00:11,333
<i> But that's all we could do.</i>

8
00:00:11,767 --> 00:00:12,767
<i> I'm very sorry.</i>

9
00:00:12,767 --> 00:00:14,367
<i>- No...
- Huh?</i>

10
00:00:14,367 --> 00:00:15,600
[SOBBING]

11
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:17,567
<i>- Doc!
- Doc!</i>

12
00:00:19,767 --> 00:00:20,767
[INHALES DEEPLY]

13
00:00:20,767 --> 00:00:23,767
<i> Brother!</i>

14
00:00:23,767 --> 00:00:26,733
<i>- Brother!
- [JUSTIN WAILING]</i>

15
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:30,733
<i>- Leon! Brother!
- Brother!</i>

16
00:00:31,267 --> 00:00:33,267
<i>- Brother! Wake up!
- Brother!</i>

17
00:00:33,267 --> 00:00:35,033
<i> Brother, please!</i>

18
00:00:35,067 --> 00:00:38,467
<i> Wake up, son. Mama's here.</i>

19
00:00:38,467 --> 00:00:40,467
<i> I will take care of you.</i>

20
00:00:40,467 --> 00:00:42,733
<i> Your sister is here too.</i>

21
00:00:43,300 --> 00:00:45,667
<i>Your brothers are here too.
Please, son.</i>

22
00:00:46,067 --> 00:00:48,733
<i> He suffered alone.</i>

23
00:00:50,067 --> 00:00:52,700
Leon and Kiko have stab wounds.

24
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:54,300
<i>The murder weapon may
have been discarded.</i>

25
00:00:54,300 --> 00:00:55,700
<i> We should look for that.</i>

26
00:00:55,700 --> 00:00:58,700
<i>All the murders were
near Hotel 88.</i>

27
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:01,000
<i>This wasn't done by
someone who's not from here.</i>

28
00:01:01,367 --> 00:01:05,733
[SOBBING]

29
00:01:07,800 --> 00:01:11,800
[CLANKING, RATTLING]

30
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:15,400
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

31
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:17,767
The hotel will halt
its operations for now.

32
00:01:18,533 --> 00:01:20,100
Effective today.

33
00:01:21,233 --> 00:01:23,333
You must've heard about
what happened, haven't you?

34
00:01:24,533 --> 00:01:27,733
We're closing the hotel
for all of our safety.

35
00:01:28,633 --> 00:01:31,567
[MARTIN] Until what happened
here gets resolved...

36
00:01:32,133 --> 00:01:34,500
the hotel will remain closed.

37
00:01:35,367 --> 00:01:37,533
Raphael will talk to you about

38
00:01:37,533 --> 00:01:39,333
your salary for this month.

39
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:44,367
[GIO] But when the hotel reopens
and you still want to return...

40
00:01:44,867 --> 00:01:47,200
you're the ones
we'll call first, okay?

41
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:49,400
- Yes, sir.
- Okay.

42
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:56,367
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

43
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:59,367
As for you, Sari...

44
00:02:00,233 --> 00:02:02,367
I'll give you
your last paycheck myself.

45
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:04,100
I'm not leaving.

46
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:06,100
[MARTIN SIGHS]

47
00:02:07,133 --> 00:02:08,500
[MARTIN] Sari.

48
00:02:09,367 --> 00:02:11,233
If the hotel's closed already,

49
00:02:11,233 --> 00:02:12,833
I won't need an assistant
anymore.

50
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:14,867
Yes, sir.

51
00:02:15,267 --> 00:02:17,200
But I won't leave you.

52
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:21,800
Even if drive me out of here,
I'll come back again and again.

53
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:22,800
Sari...

54
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:25,167
Sir, I just want to help you.

55
00:02:25,167 --> 00:02:27,800
I've gotten close with
the people here in the hotel,

56
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:29,633
so I won't leave you.

57
00:02:29,633 --> 00:02:31,200
Go home.

58
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:34,800
I can't let anything bad
happen to you too.

59
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:41,767
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

60
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:50,733
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

61
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:12,767
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

62
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:34,767
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

63
00:03:47,567 --> 00:03:49,567
[FLOWERS RUSTLING]

64
00:03:49,567 --> 00:03:50,633
[FRIDA] Just put it there.
Thank you.

65
00:03:50,633 --> 00:03:52,633
- Okay, ma'am.
- Thank you.

66
00:03:52,633 --> 00:03:53,633
[JUSTIN] Leave that to me.

67
00:03:53,633 --> 00:03:54,600
[LUNA] Thank you.

68
00:04:01,900 --> 00:04:05,267
Luna, just let the maid
arrange that.

69
00:04:05,267 --> 00:04:06,400
It's okay, Mom.

70
00:04:06,667 --> 00:04:08,233
I can do it myself.

71
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:12,967
[JADE] Luna, Mom,
I'm just going to visit Leon.

72
00:04:12,967 --> 00:04:16,767
I just need to fix some papers
so we can finally take him home.

73
00:04:17,333 --> 00:04:18,633
[LUNA] You're not leaving, Jade!

74
00:04:18,633 --> 00:04:20,500
Luna, Luna...

75
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:22,600
Huh? Sister...

76
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,800
I need to be with Leon--

77
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:26,633
You won't be leaving!
You're not leaving this house.

78
00:04:26,633 --> 00:04:27,833
[FRIDA] Luna.

79
00:04:28,267 --> 00:04:30,800
Jade just needs to take care
of some papers.

80
00:04:31,433 --> 00:04:32,600
Sister...

81
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:33,733
[JUSTIN] I'm here to help you.

82
00:04:33,733 --> 00:04:35,433
Mom, she can't go out!

83
00:04:35,433 --> 00:04:38,600
Everyone who leaves this house
never comes back, right?

84
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:40,000
- Sister!
- She can't leave!

85
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,500
- She can't get out!
- What are you saying?!

86
00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:43,900
Pull yourself together! Can you?

87
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:45,267
- Jade.
- [LUNA BREATHES DEEPLY]

88
00:04:45,267 --> 00:04:46,900
[JADE] Sorry, Mom, but...

89
00:04:46,900 --> 00:04:50,733
this will be my last moments
with my big brother.

90
00:04:50,733 --> 00:04:51,700
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

91
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:53,900
But you don't have
to shout at your sister.

92
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:55,233
[JADE] Okay, fine.

93
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:58,400
If she can't handle seeing Leon,

94
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:00,367
then fine, I'll let her.

95
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:03,400
But please, don't deprive me
of my last moments

96
00:05:03,433 --> 00:05:05,800
to be with my brother.

97
00:05:06,367 --> 00:05:08,967
[JADE] We have different ways
of dealing with this.

98
00:05:09,367 --> 00:05:11,500
I let you do you, so please...

99
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:12,500
[LUNA INHALES SHARPLY]

100
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:14,333
Let me do me!

101
00:05:14,767 --> 00:05:17,067
[LUNA EXHALES DEEPLY]

102
00:05:17,067 --> 00:05:18,433
I'll get going now, Mom.

103
00:05:18,433 --> 00:05:19,600
[LUNA] Jade.

104
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:20,967
- Jade!
- It's okay, Luna.

105
00:05:22,433 --> 00:05:23,833
It's okay.

106
00:05:23,833 --> 00:05:26,967
[LUNA BREATHING HEAVILY]

107
00:05:26,967 --> 00:05:28,433
[SNIFFLES]

108
00:05:28,433 --> 00:05:33,400
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

109
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:34,567
[CELLPHONE BEEPING]

110
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:35,600
Please...

111
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:36,767
[INHALES SHARPLY]

112
00:05:36,767 --> 00:05:39,400
[MARTIN] Raphie said he'd come
with us to the Almazans.

113
00:05:39,700 --> 00:05:40,700
Okay.

114
00:05:41,667 --> 00:05:43,633
[MARTIN] Are you calling Luna?

115
00:05:45,433 --> 00:05:47,067
Yes, but she's not answering.

116
00:05:48,667 --> 00:05:51,667
Is there anything
we need to bring them?

117
00:05:51,667 --> 00:05:55,067
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

118
00:05:55,067 --> 00:05:56,867
[GIO] Sir Henri,
what brings you here?

119
00:05:57,067 --> 00:05:59,067
I'm here to tell you that

120
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:00,900
we've gone around
your property already.

121
00:06:00,900 --> 00:06:03,467
But Leon's killer left
no traces behind.

122
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,333
Not even a single trace?

123
00:06:06,333 --> 00:06:08,300
Your opponent seems to be smart.

124
00:06:09,533 --> 00:06:11,667
The only key to this case
would be Kiko.

125
00:06:12,700 --> 00:06:15,933
We'd know more if he saw
or recognized his attacker.

126
00:06:15,933 --> 00:06:18,900
But we don't know when
our brother will wake up.

127
00:06:20,433 --> 00:06:22,433
We have to wait then.

128
00:06:22,433 --> 00:06:29,400
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

129
00:06:36,433 --> 00:06:39,433
[BELLS CHIMING]

130
00:06:39,433 --> 00:06:46,400
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

131
00:06:48,867 --> 00:06:50,433
[SNIFFLES]

132
00:06:53,867 --> 00:06:54,967
[SNIFFLES]

133
00:06:58,833 --> 00:07:00,800
[SNIFFLES]

134
00:07:01,433 --> 00:07:05,433
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

135
00:07:05,433 --> 00:07:11,800
[WHIMPERING]

136
00:07:20,467 --> 00:07:27,433
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

137
00:07:27,867 --> 00:07:29,867
[INHALES SHARPLY, CLEARS THROAT]

138
00:07:29,867 --> 00:07:34,100
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

139
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:36,067
Martin, Gio.

140
00:07:38,700 --> 00:07:40,800
[MARTIN] You haven't let
other visitors in yet?

141
00:07:42,833 --> 00:07:45,833
Mom told us to keep it between
family members for now.

142
00:07:45,833 --> 00:07:52,800
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

143
00:07:53,700 --> 00:07:54,833
[FRIDA] You!

144
00:07:55,467 --> 00:07:57,867
You have no right to come here.

145
00:07:57,867 --> 00:07:59,667
You said...

146
00:08:00,533 --> 00:08:01,933
that he was okay!

147
00:08:01,933 --> 00:08:04,533
You told us that he was
coming home to us!

148
00:08:04,533 --> 00:08:06,133
You lied!

149
00:08:06,533 --> 00:08:07,900
[JUSTIN] Mom, that's enough.

150
00:08:09,167 --> 00:08:12,767
If you had only let me talk
to him when he called,

151
00:08:12,767 --> 00:08:14,933
then I could've saved him!

152
00:08:14,933 --> 00:08:17,533
He'd be here with me right now!

153
00:08:17,533 --> 00:08:19,533
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

154
00:08:19,533 --> 00:08:20,900
I'm sorry, Auntie.

155
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:24,633
Your apology can't do anything!

156
00:08:24,633 --> 00:08:29,233
Your apology won't
bring back my son's life!

157
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:31,700
Leave!

158
00:08:31,700 --> 00:08:33,667
Leave! Get out!

159
00:08:35,267 --> 00:08:38,833
[FRIDA] I don't want to see you
and your brothers here!

160
00:08:39,267 --> 00:08:41,633
Leave!

161
00:08:41,633 --> 00:08:42,633
[FRIDA PANTING]

162
00:08:42,633 --> 00:08:44,267
[FRIDA] Leave!

163
00:08:44,267 --> 00:08:51,267
[FRIDA SOBBING]

164
00:08:51,267 --> 00:08:55,867
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

165
00:08:55,900 --> 00:08:57,867
Condolences, Jade.

166
00:08:58,300 --> 00:08:59,633
I'm very sorry.

167
00:08:59,633 --> 00:09:01,833
But you have to go.

168
00:09:04,733 --> 00:09:06,100
Brother, let's go.

169
00:09:10,867 --> 00:09:17,167
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

170
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:23,467
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

171
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:26,267
[LEON]<i> I know you're the
</i> best person for the job.

172
00:09:26,833 --> 00:09:28,167
<i> I know you.</i>

173
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:30,400
<i>I know your dedication when
it comes to things like this.</i>

174
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:32,900
<i>Even though I'm busy with
the businesses Dad left behind,</i>

175
00:09:32,900 --> 00:09:35,467
<i>I'll support you with
whatever help you need.</i>

176
00:09:36,567 --> 00:09:37,667
[MARTIN] Leon, come on.

177
00:09:37,667 --> 00:09:40,000
<i> - Come on, please. Let's go!
- No. Leave me.</i>

178
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,933
<i>- Leon, let's go! Please!
- Martin, leave me.</i>

179
00:09:41,933 --> 00:09:44,633
<i> - Please, Leon! Let's go!
- Just go, Martin!</i>

180
00:09:51,033 --> 00:09:52,433
<i> Please...</i>

181
00:09:53,867 --> 00:09:55,267
<i> Just leave me here.</i>

182
00:09:55,533 --> 00:09:57,767
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

183
00:09:57,767 --> 00:09:59,433
You're so stupid! So stupid!

184
00:09:59,433 --> 00:10:00,833
Martin, you're so stupid!

185
00:10:00,833 --> 00:10:02,700
- You're so stupid!
- [BLOWS LANDING]

186
00:10:02,733 --> 00:10:04,900
You're so stupid, Martin!

187
00:10:04,900 --> 00:10:06,900
- Let go of me!
- You're only hurting yourself!

188
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:08,400
I said let go of me!

189
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:10,067
Is this because you're
blaming yourself

190
00:10:10,067 --> 00:10:11,800
for your friend's death?

191
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:13,533
You didn't do anything wrong,
Martin.

192
00:10:13,533 --> 00:10:14,800
You wouldn't understand.

193
00:10:15,467 --> 00:10:17,700
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

194
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:18,967
You want to get hurt?

195
00:10:18,967 --> 00:10:20,400
- Here!
- [BLOW LANDS]

196
00:10:20,967 --> 00:10:22,067
[GRUNTING]

197
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:23,900
Let go!

198
00:10:23,900 --> 00:10:25,633
Gio, let go of me!

199
00:10:25,633 --> 00:10:27,467
Even if your hands
start bleeding,

200
00:10:27,467 --> 00:10:29,033
- [SCREAMING]
- you still didn't kill him!

201
00:10:29,033 --> 00:10:30,800
[MARTIN BREATHING HEAVILY]

202
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:32,533
You're not the one
who stabbed Leon!

203
00:10:32,533 --> 00:10:34,767
- You didn't end his life!
- Let go of me!

204
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:38,767
I should've brought him home!

205
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:42,433
I had a chance to save him,
but I didn't!

206
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:45,000
It's the same thing!

207
00:10:45,767 --> 00:10:47,133
I should've done
the right thing

208
00:10:47,133 --> 00:10:48,467
so he'd still be alive!

209
00:10:48,467 --> 00:10:50,367
You only did what
he asked you to do!

210
00:10:50,367 --> 00:10:52,100
You didn't know that
would happen to him, right?

211
00:10:52,100 --> 00:10:53,767
But it's still not enough!

212
00:10:53,767 --> 00:10:56,700
What I did wasn't enough!
It's always like that!

213
00:10:56,933 --> 00:10:58,467
Look at Kiko...

214
00:10:58,467 --> 00:11:00,667
even our little brother
ended up in danger.

215
00:11:00,667 --> 00:11:03,367
But if I hadn't failed,
Leon would still be alive!

216
00:11:03,367 --> 00:11:05,533
My best friend
would still be alive!

217
00:11:05,533 --> 00:11:07,567
- Don't think like that!
- He'd still be alive!

218
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:09,767
Don't blame yourself for
what happened to your brother

219
00:11:09,767 --> 00:11:10,967
and your friend!

220
00:11:11,633 --> 00:11:12,700
It's all my fault.

221
00:11:12,700 --> 00:11:14,000
It's all my fault, Gio!

222
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:16,467
Don't blame yourself for
what happened to Leon.

223
00:11:16,933 --> 00:11:18,533
Because this isn't about you!

224
00:11:19,433 --> 00:11:20,800
It's not about you, Martin!

225
00:11:21,167 --> 00:11:23,167
He died because of bad people!

226
00:11:23,167 --> 00:11:24,700
Wherever Leon is now,

227
00:11:24,700 --> 00:11:26,500
he'd tell you it's not
your fault!

228
00:11:27,033 --> 00:11:28,733
You want to do the right thing?

229
00:11:29,900 --> 00:11:31,633
Instead of punishing yourself...

230
00:11:31,633 --> 00:11:33,800
Give Leon's death dignity
and justice!

231
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:37,067
That's the Martin I know.

232
00:11:39,700 --> 00:11:41,500
That's the Martin Leon knew!

233
00:11:41,533 --> 00:11:48,467
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

234
00:11:49,567 --> 00:11:50,933
[MUSIC STOPS]

235
00:11:51,533 --> 00:11:52,767
[THUDS]

236
00:11:55,867 --> 00:12:02,833
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

237
00:12:08,033 --> 00:12:09,567
It's not your fault.

238
00:12:11,033 --> 00:12:16,033
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

239
00:12:16,067 --> 00:12:17,200
You're okay.

240
00:12:19,567 --> 00:12:21,100
You'll be okay.

241
00:12:21,633 --> 00:12:27,900
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

242
00:12:33,233 --> 00:12:34,533
[CHESKA] Bro.

243
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:36,967
Bro, wake up.

244
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:40,667
You've been resting
for too long.

245
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,167
[GEORGINA] Son...

246
00:12:44,967 --> 00:12:46,200
Wake up.

247
00:12:47,167 --> 00:12:48,767
Mama will take care of you.

248
00:12:49,133 --> 00:12:51,233
Then you'll get stronger, okay?

249
00:12:51,233 --> 00:12:53,067
Because we are going home.

250
00:12:58,600 --> 00:13:00,067
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

251
00:13:00,067 --> 00:13:01,500
Why, Cheska?

252
00:13:02,267 --> 00:13:04,700
Is there a problem
with going home?

253
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:09,000
I just remembered, Ma...

254
00:13:11,233 --> 00:13:16,633
how will Kiko accept
what happened to Leon?

255
00:13:16,633 --> 00:13:20,633
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

256
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:21,967
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

257
00:13:23,633 --> 00:13:24,967
I don't know either.

258
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:29,600
But I don't want to think
about that for now.

259
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:32,667
What matters to me is that
your brother wakes up.

260
00:13:36,700 --> 00:13:37,933
He will wake up.

261
00:13:39,133 --> 00:13:40,267
You'll wake up, right?

262
00:13:40,267 --> 00:13:41,667
You're strong.

263
00:13:44,767 --> 00:13:48,000
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

264
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:49,033
Ma.

265
00:13:54,567 --> 00:13:55,633
Kiko?

266
00:13:55,967 --> 00:13:57,100
[GEORGINA] Son.

267
00:13:57,633 --> 00:13:58,933
- Son, Kiko?
- Kiko.

268
00:14:00,267 --> 00:14:01,667
- Doc!
- Son.

269
00:14:02,700 --> 00:14:04,833
- Doc, nurse!
- Kiko.

270
00:14:04,833 --> 00:14:07,033
- Go ahead, call them.
- Wait, Ma.

271
00:14:07,033 --> 00:14:08,100
Son?

272
00:14:08,633 --> 00:14:10,700
Can you hear me, son?

273
00:14:11,567 --> 00:14:12,633
Son?

274
00:14:13,633 --> 00:14:15,000
How are you feeling?

275
00:14:17,167 --> 00:14:18,267
Uh, Doc...

276
00:14:19,033 --> 00:14:20,733
You already checked me.

277
00:14:21,900 --> 00:14:22,967
It just...

278
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:25,667
...hurts a bit.

279
00:14:25,667 --> 00:14:27,800
But my body doesn't hurt
that much anymore.

280
00:14:28,300 --> 00:14:29,700
[DOCTOR] Okay.

281
00:14:29,700 --> 00:14:32,200
Because of his injuries,

282
00:14:32,667 --> 00:14:34,733
he needs to take care
of himself.

283
00:14:35,300 --> 00:14:38,733
No sudden movements
until he fully adjusts.

284
00:14:38,733 --> 00:14:40,867
- Okay?
- Yes, Doc.

285
00:14:41,333 --> 00:14:42,667
It's okay, Doc.

286
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,867
- Alright.
- How about...

287
00:14:44,867 --> 00:14:46,133
Leon?

288
00:14:46,700 --> 00:14:48,600
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

289
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:49,667
Uh...

290
00:14:49,667 --> 00:14:50,900
I'll leave you for now.

291
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:58,167
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

292
00:14:58,167 --> 00:15:00,067
- Kiko!
- [MARTIN] Kiko!

293
00:15:00,067 --> 00:15:01,867
Oh my God! Thank you!

294
00:15:01,900 --> 00:15:03,767
- You're awake!
- Ouch, Martin! Easy!

295
00:15:05,100 --> 00:15:06,233
Sorry.

296
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:08,967
[GIO] Get stronger, okay?

297
00:15:08,967 --> 00:15:10,167
It hurts.

298
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:12,800
Where's...

299
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:13,867
Where's Leon?

300
00:15:13,867 --> 00:15:17,367
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

301
00:15:17,367 --> 00:15:18,667
Where is he?

302
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,667
[MARTIN BREATHES HEAVILY]

303
00:15:27,033 --> 00:15:28,367
Where is Leon?

304
00:15:28,367 --> 00:15:29,867
Can I go see him?

305
00:15:29,867 --> 00:15:31,300
I need to talk to him.

306
00:15:33,867 --> 00:15:34,933
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

307
00:15:35,333 --> 00:15:39,033
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

308
00:15:45,867 --> 00:15:46,867
What now?!

309
00:15:47,633 --> 00:15:48,767
Why isn't anyone answering?

310
00:15:48,767 --> 00:15:50,300
I've been asking
for a while now.

311
00:15:51,533 --> 00:15:52,867
Kiko...

312
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:56,933
You need to get some rest
so you can recover quickly.

313
00:15:57,667 --> 00:15:58,867
I know that.

314
00:15:58,867 --> 00:16:05,833
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

315
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:11,800
[MARTIN SIGHS]

316
00:16:14,700 --> 00:16:15,867
Leon is gone.

317
00:16:15,867 --> 00:16:19,500
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

318
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:20,567
W-What?

319
00:16:21,800 --> 00:16:23,700
Is he home already?

320
00:16:27,633 --> 00:16:29,267
Leon is dead, Kiko.

321
00:16:30,633 --> 00:16:32,600
His body couldn't handle
everything he went through.

322
00:16:33,733 --> 00:16:34,767
No.

323
00:16:35,333 --> 00:16:36,533
No.

324
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:39,833
Gio, t-that's not funny.

325
00:16:39,833 --> 00:16:41,500
That's a terrible joke. [SOBS]

326
00:16:41,933 --> 00:16:43,733
- I'm not joking, Kiko.
- [KIKO SNIFFLES]

327
00:16:43,733 --> 00:16:47,333
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

328
00:16:47,333 --> 00:16:48,433
Martin?

329
00:16:54,333 --> 00:16:55,367
[EXHALES]

330
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:01,500
That's not true! [SOBBING]

331
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:04,500
We were together!
That's not true! [SOBS]

332
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:05,467
Ma!

333
00:17:05,467 --> 00:17:07,833
[CRYING, SOBBING]

334
00:17:07,833 --> 00:17:09,000
Cheska, what is it?!

335
00:17:10,533 --> 00:17:12,633
Tell me the truth.
What happened?!

336
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:16,933
Leon didn't make it.

337
00:17:16,933 --> 00:17:22,800
[SOBBING, BAWLING]

338
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:25,733
Ma, I told him not to let go.

339
00:17:25,733 --> 00:17:27,433
We were supposed
to leave together

340
00:17:27,433 --> 00:17:29,733
and come back together.
[SOBS]

341
00:17:29,733 --> 00:17:31,833
Why did he let go, Ma?!

342
00:17:31,833 --> 00:17:34,600
Why did it have to be like that?
[CRYING]

343
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:36,333
What? Is it true?!

344
00:17:36,333 --> 00:17:38,767
Is what you're saying true?!

345
00:17:38,767 --> 00:17:39,867
[KIKO] Ma!

346
00:17:40,533 --> 00:17:42,900
[KIKO CRYING]
Tell me...

347
00:17:42,900 --> 00:17:45,633
[SOBBING, CRYING]

348
00:17:45,633 --> 00:17:48,933
This is all my fault!
This is all my fault.

349
00:17:48,967 --> 00:17:52,900
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

350
00:17:52,900 --> 00:17:56,567
[SOBBING, CRYING]

351
00:17:56,567 --> 00:17:58,567
That's why he didn't want
to leave me.

352
00:17:59,800 --> 00:18:01,700
[GIO] About what time
do you think the test results

353
00:18:01,700 --> 00:18:03,100
from earlier will come out?

354
00:18:03,100 --> 00:18:04,600
Probably in a little while.

355
00:18:05,067 --> 00:18:06,333
[GIO] Later?

356
00:18:09,033 --> 00:18:10,000
[GIO] Sir.

357
00:18:10,633 --> 00:18:11,867
Gio, how are you all doing?

358
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:14,500
We heard Kiko is awake.

359
00:18:15,333 --> 00:18:16,833
Can we talk to him now?

360
00:18:19,933 --> 00:18:21,400
Does it have to be now?

361
00:18:22,433 --> 00:18:25,067
He just found out
about Leon too.

362
00:18:25,933 --> 00:18:27,367
I'm sorry, Gio.

363
00:18:28,567 --> 00:18:31,100
But if he can tell us
who hurt them,

364
00:18:31,667 --> 00:18:34,333
we can protect
your family sooner.

365
00:18:34,733 --> 00:18:38,100
And we can bring justice faster
for what happened to them

366
00:18:38,100 --> 00:18:40,367
and to any other
possible victims.

367
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:42,400
Okay, sir.

368
00:18:43,133 --> 00:18:44,400
But...

369
00:18:44,700 --> 00:18:46,467
please go easy on him, okay?

370
00:18:47,933 --> 00:18:49,400
My brother is still weak.

371
00:18:53,767 --> 00:18:55,067
Kiko is awake!

372
00:18:55,100 --> 00:18:57,100
[JADE] Thank God!
In that case, let's go!

373
00:18:57,100 --> 00:18:58,600
This is what we've been
waiting for.

374
00:18:58,600 --> 00:19:01,133
[FRIDA] No!
I'll go. You all stay here.

375
00:19:01,133 --> 00:19:02,700
- [JUSTIN] But, Mom--
- Is this still because

376
00:19:02,700 --> 00:19:04,600
you're blaming Martin
and his family?

377
00:19:04,600 --> 00:19:06,967
[JUSTIN] Mom,
we need to set all that aside!

378
00:19:06,967 --> 00:19:08,100
Kiko is the only one
who can tell us

379
00:19:08,100 --> 00:19:09,800
what really happened
to him and Leon!

380
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:11,967
That's why I'm going
by myself.

381
00:19:13,133 --> 00:19:15,700
Mom, we're coming with you
whether you like it or not.

382
00:19:15,700 --> 00:19:16,800
This is all for Leon.

383
00:19:16,800 --> 00:19:18,567
- Don't leave us behind.
- No one's going anywhere!

384
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:21,900
- Luna?
- No one's going anywhere!

385
00:19:22,733 --> 00:19:23,900
[FRIDA] Luna.

386
00:19:23,900 --> 00:19:25,633
- It's okay. You can stay.
- No! No!

387
00:19:25,633 --> 00:19:27,033
- If you don't want to go--
- No, Ma! No.

388
00:19:27,033 --> 00:19:29,133
No matter what Kiko says,
it won't change anything

389
00:19:29,167 --> 00:19:30,333
because Leon is dead!

390
00:19:30,333 --> 00:19:32,900
Luna, this is important!
Yes, Leon is dead,

391
00:19:32,900 --> 00:19:35,167
- but we need to talk!
- [LUNA] I don't care!

392
00:19:35,167 --> 00:19:36,800
[SOBS] There's nothing
anyone can do anymore!

393
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:38,767
I don't care!
No one's leaving!

394
00:19:38,767 --> 00:19:40,833
Luna, what's happening to you?
Are you losing your mind?

395
00:19:40,833 --> 00:19:42,967
Luna, if you don't want to go,
that's fine.

396
00:19:42,967 --> 00:19:46,000
- We need to go there.
- Don't you understand?!

397
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:48,767
[SOBBING] What's happening?!

398
00:19:48,767 --> 00:19:50,833
[JUSTIN] Whether you like it
or not, I'll go.

399
00:19:50,833 --> 00:19:53,700
[WAILING] Justin!

400
00:19:53,700 --> 00:19:55,833
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

401
00:19:55,833 --> 00:19:57,433
- Mom...
- Are you okay?

402
00:19:57,433 --> 00:20:00,067
- [BREATHING HEAVILY, CRYING]
- Are you okay?

403
00:20:00,067 --> 00:20:01,700
- Luna...
- Luna, are you okay?

404
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:02,933
- Luna, I'm sorry.
- A brown bag!

405
00:20:02,967 --> 00:20:04,800
- Get a brown bag!
- It's okay.

406
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:07,033
- Justin...
- Luna, breathe! Breathe!

407
00:20:07,033 --> 00:20:08,867
- Breathe! Just breathe!
- [BREATHING HEAVILY]

408
00:20:08,867 --> 00:20:10,800
[FRIDA] Okay,
we're not going anymore.

409
00:20:10,800 --> 00:20:12,467
We're staying.
No one's leaving!

410
00:20:12,467 --> 00:20:15,567
[SOBBING, BREATHING HEAVILY]

411
00:20:15,567 --> 00:20:16,600
[FRIDA] It's okay.

412
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:22,200
[SOBBING, CRYING]

413
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:24,467
It's okay, it's okay.
We're going to be okay.

414
00:20:25,633 --> 00:20:26,633
It's okay, it's okay.

415
00:20:28,467 --> 00:20:30,167
Kiko, don't push yourself.

416
00:20:30,967 --> 00:20:32,467
Sir Henri can always come back.

417
00:20:32,467 --> 00:20:34,333
No, I can do this.

418
00:20:35,533 --> 00:20:37,000
This is for Leon.

419
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:39,433
I'm sorry, Kiko.

420
00:20:39,433 --> 00:20:41,100
We just need to know
what happened.

421
00:20:43,567 --> 00:20:45,433
I was walking through
the woods...

422
00:20:47,033 --> 00:20:48,600
on my way back to Hotel 88.

423
00:20:51,433 --> 00:20:53,367
I was already on my way back.

424
00:20:55,467 --> 00:20:57,400
But then I heard rustling.

425
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:59,067
[LEAVES RUSTLING]

426
00:20:59,967 --> 00:21:03,167
[KIKO] At first, I ignored it
because I didn't see anything.

427
00:21:03,633 --> 00:21:05,533
But the second time,

428
00:21:06,167 --> 00:21:08,067
I got scared so I ran.

429
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:09,867
Until...

430
00:21:09,867 --> 00:21:12,200
I looked back
and didn't notice...

431
00:21:12,900 --> 00:21:14,267
the man was already there.

432
00:21:14,267 --> 00:21:16,933
I bumped into him and fell.

433
00:21:17,567 --> 00:21:19,433
He was about to stab me.

434
00:21:20,233 --> 00:21:21,633
But I managed to run away.

435
00:21:23,033 --> 00:21:24,500
Do you remember
what he looked like?

436
00:21:27,500 --> 00:21:29,233
A tall man...

437
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:33,167
...with long hair.

438
00:21:33,167 --> 00:21:39,467
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

439
00:21:39,467 --> 00:21:41,033
When I ran,

440
00:21:41,033 --> 00:21:42,467
he chased me again.

441
00:21:43,033 --> 00:21:44,467
[SCREAMING]

442
00:21:44,467 --> 00:21:46,633
[KIKO] He was about
to stab me in the back,

443
00:21:46,633 --> 00:21:48,233
but I dodged it.

444
00:21:51,033 --> 00:21:52,933
[GRUNTING]

445
00:21:52,933 --> 00:21:54,233
[SANDRO GRUNTS]

446
00:21:54,233 --> 00:21:57,133
- [HACK SWISH]
- [GRUNTING]

447
00:21:57,133 --> 00:22:00,100
[KIKO] Until he caught me
and threw me into a tree.

448
00:22:00,433 --> 00:22:02,100
- [GRUNTS]
- [BODY THUDS]

449
00:22:02,667 --> 00:22:05,000
He was looking
for something from me.

450
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:07,500
<i> Where is my map?!</i>

451
00:22:10,600 --> 00:22:13,200
He was supposed to stab me,
but...

452
00:22:15,633 --> 00:22:17,133
- Leon arrived.
- [LEON SCREAMING]

453
00:22:17,133 --> 00:22:18,033
- [THWACKS]
- [GRUNTS]

454
00:22:18,033 --> 00:22:20,433
[KIKO] He hit the man
with a stone.

455
00:22:20,433 --> 00:22:21,667
[SANDRO GROANING]

456
00:22:22,733 --> 00:22:25,467
We don't even know
how Leon got there.

457
00:22:28,567 --> 00:22:30,567
Maybe he was really
on his way home.

458
00:22:30,567 --> 00:22:33,100
Because he already found out
that someone else killed Juan.

459
00:22:34,233 --> 00:22:36,100
[MARTIN] But in the
woods area of the hotel?

460
00:22:38,267 --> 00:22:39,600
In the eyes of the law...

461
00:22:40,333 --> 00:22:41,433
...he escaped.

462
00:22:42,733 --> 00:22:45,367
So if he was really going home,

463
00:22:45,367 --> 00:22:47,367
he wouldn't take
the normal route.

464
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:52,000
Did Leon tell you anything else?

465
00:22:53,033 --> 00:22:55,267
Everything happened so fast.

466
00:22:55,267 --> 00:22:57,100
When we were running,

467
00:22:58,533 --> 00:23:00,267
we managed to hide
behind a tree.

468
00:23:04,633 --> 00:23:07,667
We saw the man go
in another direction.

469
00:23:09,467 --> 00:23:11,233
We were about to leave,
but...

470
00:23:13,533 --> 00:23:14,733
[PANTING]

471
00:23:14,733 --> 00:23:16,067
- [STABS]
- [SANDRO GRUNTS]

472
00:23:16,067 --> 00:23:17,467
<i>- Leon!
- [LEON] Kiko!</i>

473
00:23:17,467 --> 00:23:18,600
<i> Go, you should run!</i>

474
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:20,400
<i> Kiko! Hurry!</i>

475
00:23:22,300 --> 00:23:25,100
But he stabbed Leon.

476
00:23:29,167 --> 00:23:30,567
He stabbed him
over and over, sir.

477
00:23:30,567 --> 00:23:31,767
There was so much blood.

478
00:23:31,767 --> 00:23:33,633
[HACK WHOOSHING]

479
00:23:33,633 --> 00:23:38,367
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

480
00:23:38,367 --> 00:23:40,100
Who is this person, Kiko?

481
00:23:43,533 --> 00:23:44,733
It's Sandro.

482
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:51,600
Sandro Soliman.

483
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:58,567
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

484
00:23:59,367 --> 00:24:00,467
He's alive?

485
00:24:03,567 --> 00:24:04,600
He's alive.

486
00:24:06,333 --> 00:24:08,067
Are you sure about this, Kiko?

487
00:24:09,633 --> 00:24:11,833
That's what Leon told me.

488
00:24:11,833 --> 00:24:13,733
And that's what I believe.

489
00:24:13,733 --> 00:24:20,700
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

490
00:24:27,567 --> 00:24:31,533
<i>I'll be watching you through
the cameras you're installing.</i>

491
00:24:32,533 --> 00:24:34,367
<i> If Sandro is still alive,</i>

492
00:24:34,367 --> 00:24:35,667
<i> that means he killed Dad.</i>

493
00:24:35,667 --> 00:24:37,667
<i> Andy and Sandro
could be working together.</i>

494
00:24:37,667 --> 00:24:38,800
<i> My gut is telling me it's him.</i>

495
00:24:39,333 --> 00:24:41,200
<i> They'll both rot in prison.</i>

496
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:42,733
We'll make sure of that, Martin.

497
00:24:42,733 --> 00:24:43,767
<i> You're planning something?</i>

498
00:24:43,767 --> 00:24:45,800
<i>I'll continue searching
for the treasure.</i>

499
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:47,000
<i> Are you serious?</i>

500
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:48,700
<i> As long as this hotel
isn't at peace,</i>

501
00:24:48,700 --> 00:24:50,300
<i> I won't leave my brothers.</i>

502
00:24:50,300 --> 00:24:51,233
<i> No!</i>

503
00:24:51,233 --> 00:24:53,733
<i>You'll go home.
We'll all go home.</i>

504
00:24:53,733 --> 00:24:55,267
<i> This place isn't safe.</i>

505
00:24:55,667 --> 00:24:56,733
<i> So why are you staying?</i>

506
00:24:56,733 --> 00:24:58,100
<i> Just think of it like...</i>

507
00:24:58,533 --> 00:25:01,100
<i> This is our last help for him.</i>

508
00:25:01,100 --> 00:25:02,267
<i> For our brothers.</i>
